Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. 22R 014222.   Posted by J. Dahlberg. olg

** AMENDED** 

- Defendant to be released only to a representative from MN Teen Challenge on 10/14/22 at 08:00 AM. Defendant to be directly transported to MN Teen Challenge. If Defendant is released without staff approval. Defendant must report back to St. Croix County Jail within 2 hours of release. 

- Defendant to sign release of information for Justice Support Center as soon as Defendant arrives at MN Teen Challenge.

- Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia. Testing upon reasonable suspicion or at the Court's directive. All costs associated with testing shall be the responsibility of the defendant.

- It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, A.R.S.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, social media including but not limited to texting, Facebook, Twitter, contact through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

If the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bail jumping.
